Citations
Date:  20/8/1924
Source:  NZ Journal of Agriculture
Author:
Vol / Page:  130
Edition:
Quote:  As to huddling, complaints have reached me regarding chicks crowding in corners of the house when being reared with colony-brooder stoves .. The huddling brings on a sweating condition, and this is fatal to chicks at any time.
